tool_description: Type form's Data API is to consult the responses submitted to a particular typeform.You can also use your data API to automatically export your results to more than 300 web services.
name: Typeform
title: Typeform

api_list.name: Response
api_list.description: This is for  getting the responses.

optional_parameters.name: since
optional_parameters.description: Date and time of the first response you want to list (responses are returned in oldest-to-newer order).

optional_parameters.name: until
optional_parameters.description: Date and time of the last response you want to list (responses are returned in oldest-to-newer order).

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: The number of responses you want to retrieve, specially useful for pagination.

optional_parameters.name: completed
optional_parameters.description: Whether you want to get completed, uncompleted entries (useful when using hidden fields to see which of your users did not finish the typeform), or both (if no completed argument is provided).

optional_parameters.name: offset
optional_parameters.description: The order number of the first row you want to retrieve, specially useful for pagination.
